The Telegraph - Calcutta : International
 Wednesday, December 18, 2002 				 Choco Beckham melts Japanese
				 	 The chocolate-covered David Beckham statue in Tokyo. (Reuters)																								Tokyo, Dec. 17 (Reuters): Hes already melted the hearts of his Japanese fans.																								Now British soccer star David Beckham is set to tantalise their taste buds as he stands three metres tall and made of milk chocolate in the middle of a busy intersection in downtown Tokyo.																								He tastes of sweet, sweet chocolate, said Kinya Murakami of Meiji Seika, the chocolate manufacturer that commissioned the statue for an advertising campaign that kicked off today.																								Meiji Seika will show the star nibbling on its chocolate almond candies in the companys commercials and posters.																								The footballing idol won Japanese hearts as England captain during the soccer World Cup in June where he was followed by hordes of screaming fans. Those fans, however, still wont be able to grab a piece of the star. The statueis not for sale. It will be on display until Christmas. 
